The paper discusses object detection in optical remote sensing images using deep learning methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also proposes a new benchmark dataset for object detection, which could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and information retrieval (cs.IR) communities. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing datasets and proposes a new large-scale dataset, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
